# Encrypt all game configuration files. Generated example games
# (games/beispiel-*.json) are gitignored and never committed — see
# specs/example-games.md.
games/*.json filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt

# Encrypt the top-level gameshow config (gameshow names, gameOrder, team settings).
# When config.json is missing or unreadable, the server writes a minimal default
# (an empty "Beispiele" gameshow); the admin "Beispiele erstellen" button or
# `npm run fixtures` then populates example games from code fixtures
# (see specs/clean-install.md and specs/example-games.md).
config.json filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt

# spellcheck-allowlist.json is intentionally NOT encrypted: it holds shareable
# vocabulary (proper nouns, brand names) + the spellcheck on/off flag, no secrets.
# Do not add a blanket `*.json filter=git-crypt` rule — see specs/spellcheck.md.
